<h2 class="bold font-l">Forte</h2>
<p class="_pmvv-vidbox-descTxt">
We meet Forte, the castle's former maestro-turned-pipe organ, who vows to keep Beast and Belle apart so he can stay this way and be Beast's only friend. </p>
</div>
<div class="video-examples-thumbs">
<a href="#video-link" data-video-id="m0fejq" data-video-descrip="In the music video for &amp;quot;Blood, Sweat and Tears&amp;quot;, the song pauses after the bridge to give way to a rendition of Buxtehude's &amp;quot;Passacaglia in D minor&amp;quot; (one of the video's many references to Hermann Hesse's &amp;quot;Demian&amp;quot;) in an eerily unnatural-looking organ, leading to the ominous climax." data-video-title="&quot;Blood, Sweat and Tears&quot;" data-video-url="https://d1w6li7s85ibls.cloudfront.net/qvbr/m0fejq_640x360p_qvbr.mp4" data-video-thumbnail="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/m0fejq.jpg" data-video-trope="Main/OminousPipeOrgan" data-video-tropename="Ominous Pipe Organ" data-video-approval="APPROVED" data-video-troper-rating="" data-video-average-rating="" data-video-rating-count="" data-video-media-sources="Music/BTS,Music/BTSUniverse" class="video-launch-link video-overlay-link video-background-image lazy-image" data-src="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/m0fejq.jpg">
<p><span class="bold">"Blood, Sweat a...</span></p>
</a>
<a href="#video-link" data-video-id="532ydd" data-video-descrip="Davy Jones in Pirates of the Caribbean: Dead Man's Chest. The only reason he's able to do it is that his ship is alive. He plays it with his beard. Which is probably inspired by Captain Nemo in 20,000 Leagues Under the Sea. Pipe organ music also features in his Leitmotif and that of his pet the Kraken." data-video-title="Davy Jones plays the Organ" data-video-url="https://d1w6li7s85ibls.cloudfront.net/qvbr/532ydd_640x360p_qvbr.mp4" data-video-thumbnail="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/515j1aua6xl_ac.jpg" data-video-trope="Main/OminousPipeOrgan" data-video-tropename="Ominous Pipe Organ" data-video-approval="APPROVED" data-video-troper-rating="" data-video-average-rating="" data-video-rating-count="" data-video-media-sources="Film/PiratesOfTheCaribbeanDeadMansChest" class="video-launch-link video-overlay-link video-background-image lazy-image" data-src="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/515j1aua6xl_ac.jpg">
